				&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan='4' style='text-align: center;' class='diff-multi'&gt;(3 intermediate revisions by the same user not shown)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 2:&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 2:&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;He realizes that postulates and derivative propositions ('words&amp;#160; explanation' [''On Nature XXV'']) cannot be debatable (we say analytic propositions are tautological), but “ If you arbitrarily reject [...] every intuitive faculty of mind, you will impute trouble to all other sensory experiences, thereby rejecting every criterion” [P.D. 24]. So, for our life completeness, living with pleasure (sensory experience), total demonstrability is not necessary, as Demetrius the Laconian says: &amp;quot; In the work entitled ''Kyriai Doxai'', Epicurus says that the [end is pleasure] [teaching that] it [needs] no demonstration&amp;quot; [''Textual Aporias'' fr. 52, Pherc 1012, Delattre].&amp;#160; His intuitive deductive ''physiologia'' has been almost strengthened by our empiric physics; nevertheless “theory can be tried out by experiment, but there is no way that leads from experiment to the birth of a theory” [A. Einstein, cit. by Vallentin A. ''Einstein'' (1965) p.105].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;He realizes that postulates and derivative propositions ('words&amp;#160; explanation' [''On Nature XXV'']) cannot be debatable (we say analytic propositions are tautological), but “ If you arbitrarily reject [...] every intuitive faculty of mind, you will impute trouble to all other sensory experiences, thereby rejecting every criterion” [P.D. 24]. So, for our life completeness, living with pleasure (sensory experience), total demonstrability is not necessary, as Demetrius the Laconian says: &amp;quot; In the work entitled ''Kyriai Doxai'', Epicurus says that the [end is pleasure] [teaching that] it [needs] no demonstration&amp;quot; [''Textual Aporias'' fr. 52, Pherc 1012, Delattre].&amp;#160; His intuitive deductive ''physiologia'' has been almost strengthened by our empiric physics; nevertheless “theory can be tried out by experiment, but there is no way that leads from experiment to the birth of a theory” [A. Einstein, cit. by Vallentin A. ''Einstein'' (1965) p.105].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurus&amp;#160; achievements&amp;#160; result from his scientific epistemology that has excluded any authoritarian dogmatism and monism but&amp;#160; fear&amp;#160; of positive law (P.D. 34, “injustice is not an evil in and by itself”), and an elementary ''prolêpsis'' of justice, “not to inflict nor allow harm” and “to benefit human interactions” (usefulness), that does not include distributive justice, nor a standard of punishment that are relative ''ypolêpseis'' that is 'agreements'. He needed a philosophy of&amp;#160; ''ataraxia'', free from vain hopes, fear of Gods and guilty feelings and a world outlook set out by limits toward ''isonomia'', balance of opposites and ''katastematik'' stable desires that we can control.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurus&amp;#160; achievements&amp;#160; result from his scientific epistemology that has excluded any authoritarian dogmatism and monism but&amp;#160; fear&amp;#160; of positive law (P.D. 34, “injustice is not an evil in and by itself”), and an elementary ''prolêpsis'' of justice, “not to inflict nor allow harm” and “to benefit human interactions” (usefulness), that does not include distributive justice, nor a standard of punishment that are relative ''ypolêpseis'' that is 'agreements'. He needed a philosophy of&amp;#160; ''ataraxia'', free from vain hopes, fear of Gods and guilty feelings and a world outlook set out by limits toward ''isonomia'', balance of opposites and ''katastematik'' stable desires that we can control.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;As Stoics reasoned necessity principle with a logical proposition - that says nothing about actual weather conditions -&amp;#160; ('tomorrow it'll raining or not raining' : it's necessary and ''tertium non datur''),&amp;#160; Epicurus likely and logically deduced that sometime necessity is not there, since 'all is necessary' is logically self confuting. Human trial-and-error synaptic links, alias soul's atoms course, are not programmed by somebody and knowledge can't define its future beliefs and our ensuing innovatory deeds.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;As Stoics reasoned necessity principle with a logical proposition - that says nothing about actual weather conditions -&amp;#160; ('tomorrow it'll raining or not raining' : it's necessary and ''tertium non datur''),&amp;#160; Epicurus likely and logically deduced that sometime necessity is not there, since 'all is necessary' is logically self confuting&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;.&amp;#160; It's the peculiar causality (self-determination) of an atoms aggregate (the soul logical indubitable movements) that makes the single atom's swerve of the aggregation be inferable, not vice versa: a 'freedom from' extraneous movements, a soul's causality against another external causality [''Nature'' Book XXV; see ''eleuthera tis en tais atomois ['''plural noun'''] keinesis'' of Diog, Oin. fr. 54:&amp;#160; “a free movement in the atoms”]&lt;/ins&gt;. Human trial-and-error synaptic links, alias soul's atoms course, are not programmed by somebody&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, &lt;/ins&gt;and knowledge can't define its future beliefs and &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;hence &lt;/ins&gt;our ensuing innovatory deeds &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; (no knowable necessity)&lt;/ins&gt;.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Total necessity would imply that '''all''' atoms have a '''linear, one-way, external causality''' Epicurus graphically designed&amp;#160; as linear&amp;#160; and parallel movement of atoms; non necessity, as a swerve, implying a crossroad/node with affirmation or negation; multiple explanation (''pleonachos tropos'') and choice imply a multiple – 'tree structure' - causality (''pleonache tes geneseos aitia'' [Pyth 87; e.g. he mistrusted too schematic astrolabes and cosmological models]), a conglomerate 'vibration' is a circuit causality or retro-action loop, where affirmation or negation act against the subject itself, under omeostasis, so as to preserve the conglomerate. Since the thought (immediate and complex atoms movement)&amp;#160; has '''negation''' capability ''antimartyrêsis'', - i.e. no one-way straight motion, so there must be there some soul atoms alternative ways/crossroads&amp;#160; (and a 'tree' choice)&amp;#160; without necessity, that is with steering (''paregklisis''/swerve) as may be watched in capillary vessels (today synapses).&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Total necessity would imply that '''all''' atoms have a '''linear, one-way, external causality''' Epicurus graphically designed&amp;#160; as linear&amp;#160; and parallel movement of atoms; non necessity, as a swerve, implying a crossroad/node with affirmation or negation; multiple explanation (''pleonachos tropos'') and choice imply a multiple – 'tree structure' - causality (''pleonache tes geneseos aitia'' [Pyth 87; e.g. he mistrusted too schematic astrolabes and cosmological models]), a conglomerate 'vibration' is a circuit causality or retro-action loop, where affirmation or negation act against the subject itself, under omeostasis, so as to preserve the conglomerate. Since the thought (immediate and complex atoms movement)&amp;#160; has '''negation''' capability ''antimartyrêsis'', - i.e. no one-way straight motion, so there must be there some soul atoms alternative ways/crossroads&amp;#160; (and a 'tree' choice)&amp;#160; without necessity, that is with steering (''paregklisis''/swerve) as may be watched in capillary vessels (today synapses).&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;It was no far-fletched&amp;#160; logicism about Physics: today Networks Theory – starting from Poincaré and Euler -&amp;#160; considers non linear causality;&amp;#160; the very artificial thought/cybernetic designs&amp;#160; a web of retro-actions/feedbacks, which say no to deterministic second principle of thermodynamics (' '''negative'''- entropy', order trend, creativity).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;It was no far-fletched&amp;#160; logicism about Physics: today Networks Theory – starting from Poincaré and Euler -&amp;#160; considers non linear causality;&amp;#160; the very artificial thought/cybernetic designs&amp;#160; a web of retro-actions/feedbacks, which say no to deterministic second principle of thermodynamics (' '''negative'''- entropy', order trend, creativity).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;A necessity theorist cannot demonstrate his opposer is wrong, since he couldn't freely be in agreement with the opposite point of view that&amp;#160; his personal necessity unfairly doesn't allow, and bestows no alternative (negation) to his way of thinking (nor the improvement of kinetic desires): “He who says that all things happen by necessity can hardly find fault with the one who denies that all happens by necessity; for on his own theory this very argument is voiced by necessity” [V.S. 40], not by independent truthfulness... We are entitled to believe our brain is able to develop its 'applications' negating some external necessities by flight or shelters.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;A necessity theorist cannot demonstrate his opposer is wrong, since he couldn't freely be in agreement with the opposite point of view that&amp;#160; his personal necessity unfairly doesn't allow, and bestows no alternative (negation) to his way of thinking (nor the improvement of kinetic desires): “He who says that all things happen by necessity can hardly find fault with the one who denies that all happens by necessity; for on his own theory this very argument is voiced by necessity” [V.S. 40], not by independent truthfulness... We are entitled to believe our brain is able to develop its 'applications' negating some external necessities by flight or shelters.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Everything happens by necessity being self-confuting and '''there is always negation''' being self-confuting too (since one is affirming it) imply that&amp;#160; ''' 'Not everything' ''' happens by necessity - as a contrary- may be true under situations; sometime is there necessity,&amp;#160; sometime necessity is not, since one can choose after his own desires [like says D.L. 134]. Non necessity, as a swerve, implies a crossroad/node&amp;#160; (instead of vessels ... today synapses)&amp;#160; with affirmation or negation; that a negation is there into one's mind one is sure, since denying is the evidence of its existence,&amp;#160; and that's enough for one's pleasure attainableness and freedom, the negation of some external causality. &amp;quot;Concentrated together [atoms], [...] are by nature capable of producing such things and starting such a process&amp;quot; [ ''On Nature'' Book XXV PHerc 697, [34. 4] ARR.; see Talk:Canon; and “mind's primitive constitution” ”with its own causality”&amp;#160; (''Perì Physeos'' VIII Pap. 1056/697/1191.7. Arrighetti)]. Since the age of two, the human being can always say no in every situation, hopefully with thoughtfulness. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Everything happens by necessity being self-confuting and '''there is always negation''' being self-confuting too (since one is affirming it) imply that&amp;#160; ''' 'Not everything' ''' happens by necessity &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;(''hip'anagkes'' of Democritus) &lt;/ins&gt;- as a contrary- may be true under situations; sometime is there necessity,&amp;#160; sometime necessity is not, since one can choose after his own desires [like says D.L. 134]. Non necessity, as a swerve, implies a crossroad/node&amp;#160; (instead of vessels ... today synapses)&amp;#160; with affirmation or negation; that a negation is there into one's mind one is sure, since denying is the evidence of its existence,&amp;#160; and that's enough for one's pleasure attainableness and freedom, the negation of some external causality. &amp;quot;Concentrated together [atoms], [...] are by nature capable of producing such things and starting such a process&amp;quot; [ ''On Nature'' Book XXV PHerc 697, [34. 4] ARR.; see Talk:Canon; and “mind's primitive constitution” ”with its own causality”&amp;#160; (''Perì Physeos'' VIII Pap. 1056/697/1191.7. Arrighetti)]. Since the age of two, the human being can always say no in every situation, hopefully with thoughtfulness. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;From the same reasoning, as one cannot determine one's necessary desires, Epicurus inferred that negation - as a constituent element of the world - implies also limitation of freedom, since swerve ''paregklisis'' - acting under minimum margin at a time ''elachiston''- , and ''isonomia'' (balancing of opposites and complementaries) clash against our atoms; so can it be theorized:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;From the same reasoning, as one cannot determine one's necessary desires, Epicurus inferred that negation - as a constituent element of the world - implies also limitation of freedom, since swerve ''paregklisis'' - acting under minimum margin at a time ''elachiston''- , and ''isonomia'' (balancing of opposites and complementaries) clash against our atoms; so can it be theorized:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The fall (eternal movement) of all atoms (not only soul's atoms) must have a non straight linear motion (i.e. have ''paregklisis''/swerve), because there is evidence of provisional agglomerates, and these atoms compounds have no straight but reticular vibrating motion, hence with rebound/negation or aggregation/affirmation; no atom is outside, since it is limited by the whole, it has an uncountable variability, but not infinite.&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The fall (eternal movement) of all atoms (not only soul's atoms) must have a non straight linear motion (i.e. have ''paregklisis''/swerve), because there is evidence of provisional agglomerates, and these atoms compounds have no straight but reticular vibrating motion, hence with rebound/negation or aggregation/affirmation; no atom is outside, since it is limited by the whole, it has an uncountable variability, but not infinite.&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Our pleasure is limited by necessary (that is invariable nervous and chemical response) body instincts, so it cannot grow, no positive freedom. That implies aloofness (by some more inward looking persons) from ambitions (infinite frustrating desires)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Our pleasure is limited by necessary (that is invariable nervous and chemical response) body instincts, so it cannot grow, no positive freedom. That implies aloofness (by some more inward looking persons) from ambitions (infinite frustrating desires)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The thought gets its own '''limited''' freedom from the swerve of atoms and simulacra limited by other simulacra:&amp;#160; prolêpseis cannot be demonstrated (axioms); logic is limited by common more or plus and ''epilogismos''; choice rises when there is a limit of an alternative (crossroad).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The thought gets its own '''limited''' freedom from the swerve of atoms and simulacra limited by other simulacra:&amp;#160; prolêpseis cannot be demonstrated (axioms); logic is limited by common more or plus and ''epilogismos''; choice rises when there is a limit of an alternative (crossroad).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Gods cannot be outside of the whole too, hence they must have atomic internal causality,&amp;#160; they cannot be devoid of swerve,&amp;#160; they cannot deny external causality and casualness, hence they cannot inspire prophets nor help mankind.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Gods cannot be outside of the whole too, hence they must have atomic internal causality,&amp;#160; they cannot be devoid of swerve,&amp;#160; they cannot deny external causality and casualness, hence they cannot inspire prophets nor help mankind&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;; if only polytheism is less determinist: one is free to choose one's corporate god (a sort of multiple 'tree structure' causality)&lt;/ins&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;''Prolêpsis/prôton ennoêma '', limit (''peras''), ''epilogismos'', practical prudence&amp;#160; (''phronêsis''), have been great results of Epicurean epistemological pragmatic recycling of Skeptics and Sophists' negativism and moral extremism, against oversimplifications of preceding philosophers lined in religion and politics of their State.&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;''Prolêpsis/prôton ennoêma '', limit (''peras''), ''epilogismos'', practical prudence&amp;#160; (''phronêsis''), have been great results of Epicurean epistemological pragmatic recycling of Skeptics and Sophists' negativism and moral extremism, against oversimplifications of preceding philosophers lined in religion and politics of their State.&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 17:&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 17:&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;We have seen that science&amp;#160; (''physiologia'') is object of search into the past experiences of&amp;#160; persons fond of knowledge, the ''philo-sophoi''. But the future and&amp;#160; hidden (''to adêlon'') purposes of people are not scientifically knowable, they are only questionable, and are the subject-matter of prudence: wise questions, frequently updated about evolving situation, readiness and flexibility of action, that is virtue (''arete''). The more wise questions are: desirability and attainability (''oroys tôn epithymiôn'', [P.D.XI]; ''tagathon men eyktêton'', [The Fourfold Remedy]; control of oneself,&amp;#160; of things and persons (a &amp;quot;disposition, of which we are master&amp;quot; [''diatesis ês êmeis kyrioi'' …] not the one &amp;quot;which is under the control of others&amp;quot; [Diog. Oin., Fr. 112 ]). Non necessary desires, compared to necessities&amp;#160; are&amp;#160; secondary and each other substituable. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;We have seen that science&amp;#160; (''physiologia'') is object of search into the past experiences of&amp;#160; persons fond of knowledge, the ''philo-sophoi''. But the future and&amp;#160; hidden (''to adêlon'') purposes of people are not scientifically knowable, they are only questionable, and are the subject-matter of prudence: wise questions, frequently updated about evolving situation, readiness and flexibility of action, that is virtue (''arete''). The more wise questions are: desirability and attainability (''oroys tôn epithymiôn'', [P.D.XI]; ''tagathon men eyktêton'', [The Fourfold Remedy]; control of oneself,&amp;#160; of things and persons (a &amp;quot;disposition, of which we are master&amp;quot; [''diatesis ês êmeis kyrioi'' …] not the one &amp;quot;which is under the control of others&amp;quot; [Diog. Oin., Fr. 112 ]). Non necessary desires, compared to necessities&amp;#160; are&amp;#160; secondary and each other substituable. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Easiness of life is almost achievable by living secluded from crowd, by justice and indulgence with servants, by not deeply getting involved into love of women, by choice of sage persons and by wary reciprocation of favors between friends&amp;#160; discussed in ''On Gifts and Gratitude'' (''Perì dôrôn kai charitos'').&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Easiness of life is almost achievable by living secluded from crowd, by justice and indulgence with servants, by not deeply getting involved into love of women, by choice of sage persons and by wary reciprocation of favors between friends&amp;#160; discussed in ''On Gifts and Gratitude'' (''Perì dôrôn kai charitos'').&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Prudence is made by questions, so most of all the Epicurean has to ask himself: “What will happen to me if that which this desire seeks is attained, and what if it is not?” [V.S. 71], putting into practice ''symmetrêsis&amp;#160; &amp;lt;kai&amp;gt; sympherônton kay asymphorôn'' [''Menoec''. 130] the “empirical calculation&amp;#160; of advantages and of harms”, and the ''eklogisis'' and&amp;#160; ''epilogismòs'', in analogy with preceding decisions. “Reckon into yourself not only about the 'more' but also about the 'less' [...]. If you got it at length, you are replete; if not at length, you are not still addicted […]&amp;#160; Is this a bafflement? You'll be alive as much easily as you lived before. [...] What we seek and by long job we compete about, we have to look into whether nothing in it is awkward or more than awkward: that is empty, these are dearly” [Sen. ''Ep'' 42, 6]. I appreciate what it is keeping up, but if it blows away, I give back it and I cut me off by my virtue” [Hor., ''Carmina'' III, 29, 41].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Prudence is made by &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;renewing &lt;/ins&gt;questions &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;and versatility&lt;/ins&gt;, so most of all the Epicurean has to ask himself: “What will happen to me if that which this desire seeks is attained, and what if it is not?” [V.S. 71], putting into practice ''symmetrêsis&amp;#160; &amp;lt;kai&amp;gt; sympherônton kay asymphorôn'' [''Menoec''. 130] the “empirical calculation&amp;#160; of advantages and of harms”, and the ''eklogisis'' and&amp;#160; ''epilogismòs'', in analogy with preceding decisions. “Reckon into yourself not only about the 'more' but also about the 'less' [...]. If you got it at length, you are replete; if not at length, you are not still addicted […]&amp;#160; Is this a bafflement? You'll be alive as much easily as you lived before. [...] What we seek and by long job we compete about, we have to look into whether nothing in it is awkward or more than awkward: that is empty, these are dearly” [Sen. ''Ep'' 42, 6]. I appreciate what it is keeping up, but if it blows away, I give back it and I cut me off by my virtue” [Hor., ''Carmina'' III, 29, 41].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;In case of impossible solution “Take up these sentences. We bother either by present or future troubles. About the present ones it's easy: if your body is free and without painful health , you wait and see, for now no work. Nobody is unlucky only by present” [Sen. ''Ep''. 13,7].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;In case of impossible solution “Take up these sentences. We bother either by present or future troubles. About the present ones it's easy: if your body is free and without painful health , you wait and see, for now no work. Nobody is unlucky only by present” [Sen. ''Ep''. 13,7].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Giampaolo zennaro</name></author>	</entry>

