				&lt;tr style='vertical-align: top;'&gt;
				&lt;td colspan='2' style=&quot;background-color: white; color:black; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;← Older revision&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td colspan='2' style=&quot;background-color: white; color:black; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Revision as of 06:01, 30 January 2015&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 1:&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 1:&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurean 'signs/designations' (''semeioseon'') are an “observable basis of analogical inference and transition by similarity (''kath' omoiotêta metabasis'') to unobserved or unobservable” [De Lacy, ''On Infer'' p. 157].&amp;#160; “... so all natures that are grasped by application acts which move toward the unobservable&amp;#160; we will see them&amp;#160; if we look at the similarities which ...” [Epicurus, ''On Nature'' XXXIV (PHerc. 1451) Col. XI].&amp;#160; “These bodies (i.e. atoms) cannot be grasped but by reason [...] They have their own forms which cannot be grasped but by reason” [Plutarch, ''Opinions of Philosophers'', about Epicurus]. Epicurus' Philosophy is more deductive (with critical awareness) than generally has been thought, modeling itself, after Euclid, by ''ai dôdeca stocheiôsis'' [U56]&amp;#160; the '''Twelve Elementary Propositions''' after Euclid intuitive postulates. 1 Matter is uncreatable, 2 Matter is Indistructible, 3 The universe consists of solid bodies and void , 4 Solid bodies are either compounds or simple, 5 The multitude of atoms is infinite, 6 The void is infinite in extent, 7 The atoms are always in motion, 8 The speed of atomic motion is uniform, 9 Motion is linear in space, vibratory in compounds&amp;#160; 10 Atoms are capable of swerving slightly at any point in space or time, 11 Atoms are characterized by three qualities, weight, shape and size,&amp;#160; 12 The number of the different shapes is not infinite, merely innumerable.&amp;#160; All former propositions are primary knowledge, secondary are derivative (from DRN books I-II, and De Witt), only ''antimartyrêsis''/falsifiability and non-counter-claim (''ouk antimartyrêsis'') are inductive.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurean 'signs/designations' (''semeioseon'') are an “observable basis of analogical inference and transition by similarity (''kath' omoiotêta metabasis'') to unobserved or unobservable” [De Lacy, ''On Infer'' p. 157].&amp;#160; “... so all natures that are grasped by application acts which move toward the unobservable&amp;#160; we will see them&amp;#160; if we look at the similarities which ...” [Epicurus, ''On Nature'' XXXIV (PHerc. 1451) Col. XI].&amp;#160; “These bodies (i.e. atoms) cannot be grasped but by reason [...] They have their own forms which cannot be grasped but by reason” [Plutarch, ''Opinions of Philosophers'', about Epicurus]. Epicurus' Philosophy is more deductive (with critical awareness) than generally has been thought, modeling itself, after Euclid, by ''ai dôdeca stocheiôsis'' [U56]&amp;#160; the '''Twelve Elementary Propositions''' after Euclid intuitive postulates. 1 Matter is uncreatable, 2 Matter is Indistructible, 3 The universe consists of solid bodies and void , 4 Solid bodies are either compounds or simple, 5 The multitude of atoms is infinite, 6 The void is infinite in extent, 7 The atoms are always in motion, 8 The speed of atomic motion is uniform, 9 Motion is linear in space, vibratory in compounds&amp;#160; 10 Atoms are capable of swerving slightly at any point in space or time, 11 Atoms are characterized by three qualities, weight, shape and size,&amp;#160; 12 The number of the different shapes is not infinite, merely innumerable.&amp;#160; All former propositions are primary knowledge, secondary are derivative (from DRN books I-II, and De Witt), only ''antimartyrêsis''/falsifiability and non-counter-claim (''ouk antimartyrêsis'') are inductive.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;He realizes that postulates and derivative propositions ('words&amp;#160; explanation' [''On Nature XXV'']) cannot be debatable (we say analytic propositions are tautological), but “ If you arbitrarily reject [...] every intuitive faculty of mind, you will impute trouble to all other sensory experiences, thereby rejecting every criterion” [P.D. 24]. So, for our life completeness, living with pleasure (sensory experience), total demonstrability is not necessary, as Demetrius the Laconian says: &amp;quot; In the work entitled ''Kyriai Doxai'', Epicurus says that the [end is pleasure] [teaching that] it [needs] no demonstration&amp;quot; [''Textual Aporias'' fr. 52, Pherc 1012, Delattre].&amp;#160; His intuitive deductive ''physiologia'' has been almost strengthened by our empiric physics; nevertheless “theory can be tried out by experiment, but there is no way that leads from experiment to the birth of a theory” [A. Einstein, cit. by Vallentin A. ''Einstein'' (1965) p.105].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;He realizes that postulates and derivative propositions ('words&amp;#160; explanation' [''On Nature XXV'']) cannot be debatable (we say analytic propositions are tautological), but “ If you arbitrarily reject [...] every intuitive faculty of mind, you will impute trouble to all other sensory experiences, thereby rejecting every criterion” [P.D. 24]. So, for our life completeness, living with pleasure (sensory experience), total demonstrability is not necessary, as Demetrius the Laconian says: &amp;quot; In the work entitled ''Kyriai Doxai'', Epicurus says that the [end is pleasure] [teaching that] it [needs] no demonstration&amp;quot; [''Textual Aporias'' fr. 52, Pherc 1012, Delattre].&amp;#160; His intuitive deductive ''physiologia'' has been almost strengthened by our empiric physics; nevertheless “theory can be tried out by experiment, but there is no way that leads from experiment to the birth of a theory” [A. Einstein, cit. by Vallentin A. ''Einstein'' (1965) p.105].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurus&amp;#160; achievements&amp;#160; result from his scientific epistemology that has excluded any authoritarian dogmatism but&amp;#160; fear&amp;#160; of positive law (P.D. 34, “injustice is not an evil in and by itself”), and an elementary ''prolêpsis'' of justice, “not to inflict nor allow harm” and “to benefit human interactions” (usefulness), that does not include distributive justice, nor a standard of punishment that are relative ''ypolêpseis'' that is 'agreements'. He needed a philosophy of&amp;#160; ''ataraxia'', free from vain hopes, fear of Gods and guilty feelings and a world outlook set out by limits toward ''isonomia'', balance of opposites and ''katastematik'' stable desires that we can control.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurus&amp;#160; achievements&amp;#160; result from his scientific epistemology that has excluded any authoritarian dogmatism &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;and monism &lt;/ins&gt;but&amp;#160; fear&amp;#160; of positive law (P.D. 34, “injustice is not an evil in and by itself”), and an elementary ''prolêpsis'' of justice, “not to inflict nor allow harm” and “to benefit human interactions” (usefulness), that does not include distributive justice, nor a standard of punishment that are relative ''ypolêpseis'' that is 'agreements'. He needed a philosophy of&amp;#160; ''ataraxia'', free from vain hopes, fear of Gods and guilty feelings and a world outlook set out by limits toward ''isonomia'', balance of opposites and ''katastematik'' stable desires that we can control.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;As Stoics reasoned necessity principle with a logical proposition - that says nothing about actual weather conditions -&amp;#160; ('tomorrow it'll raining or not raining' : it's necessary and ''tertium non datur''),&amp;#160; Epicurus likely and logically deduced that sometime necessity is not there, since 'all is necessary' is logically self confuting. Human trial-and-error synaptic links, alias soul's atoms course, are not programmed by somebody and knowledge can't define its future beliefs and our ensuing innovatory deeds.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;As Stoics reasoned necessity principle with a logical proposition - that says nothing about actual weather conditions -&amp;#160; ('tomorrow it'll raining or not raining' : it's necessary and ''tertium non datur''),&amp;#160; Epicurus likely and logically deduced that sometime necessity is not there, since 'all is necessary' is logically self confuting. Human trial-and-error synaptic links, alias soul's atoms course, are not programmed by somebody and knowledge can't define its future beliefs and our ensuing innovatory deeds.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Total necessity would imply that '''all''' atoms have a '''linear, one-way, external causality''' Epicurus graphically designed&amp;#160; as linear&amp;#160; and parallel movement of atoms; non necessity, as a swerve, implying a crossroad/node with affirmation or negation; multiple explanation and choice imply a 'tree' causality, a conglomerate 'vibration' is a circuit causality or retro-action loop, where affirmation or negation act against the subject itself, under omeostasis, so as to preserve the conglomerate. Since the thought (immediate and complex atoms movement)&amp;#160; has '''negation''' capability ''antimartyrêsis'', - i.e. no one-way straight motion, so there must be there some soul atoms alternative ways/crossroads&amp;#160; (and a 'tree' choice)&amp;#160; without necessity, that is with steering (''paregklisis''/swerve) as may be watched in capillary vessels (today synapses).&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Total necessity would imply that '''all''' atoms have a '''linear, one-way, external causality''' Epicurus graphically designed&amp;#160; as linear&amp;#160; and parallel movement of atoms; non necessity, as a swerve, implying a crossroad/node with affirmation or negation; multiple explanation &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;(''pleonachos tropos'') &lt;/ins&gt;and choice imply a &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;multiple – &lt;/ins&gt;'tree &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;structure&lt;/ins&gt;' &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;- &lt;/ins&gt;causality &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;(''pleonache tes geneseos aitia'' [Pyth 87; e.g. he mistrusted too schematic astrolabes and cosmological models])&lt;/ins&gt;, a conglomerate 'vibration' is a circuit causality or retro-action loop, where affirmation or negation act against the subject itself, under omeostasis, so as to preserve the conglomerate. Since the thought (immediate and complex atoms movement)&amp;#160; has '''negation''' capability ''antimartyrêsis'', - i.e. no one-way straight motion, so there must be there some soul atoms alternative ways/crossroads&amp;#160; (and a 'tree' choice)&amp;#160; without necessity, that is with steering (''paregklisis''/swerve) as may be watched in capillary vessels (today synapses).&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;It was no far-fletched&amp;#160; logicism about Physics: today Networks Theory – starting from Poincaré and Euler -&amp;#160; considers non linear causality;&amp;#160; the very artificial thought/cybernetic designs&amp;#160; a web of retro-actions/feedbacks, which say no to deterministic second principle of thermodynamics (' '''negative'''- entropy', order trend, creativity).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;It was no far-fletched&amp;#160; logicism about Physics: today Networks Theory – starting from Poincaré and Euler -&amp;#160; considers non linear causality;&amp;#160; the very artificial thought/cybernetic designs&amp;#160; a web of retro-actions/feedbacks, which say no to deterministic second principle of thermodynamics (' '''negative'''- entropy', order trend, creativity).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;A necessity theorist cannot demonstrate his opposer is wrong, since he couldn't freely be in agreement with the opposite point of view that&amp;#160; his personal necessity unfairly doesn't allow, and bestows no alternative (negation) to his way of thinking (nor the improvement of kinetic desires): “He who says that all things happen by necessity can hardly find fault with the one who denies that all happens by necessity; for on his own theory this very argument is voiced by necessity” [V.S. 40], not by independent truthfulness... We are entitled to believe our brain is able to develop its 'applications' negating some external necessities by flight or shelters.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;A necessity theorist cannot demonstrate his opposer is wrong, since he couldn't freely be in agreement with the opposite point of view that&amp;#160; his personal necessity unfairly doesn't allow, and bestows no alternative (negation) to his way of thinking (nor the improvement of kinetic desires): “He who says that all things happen by necessity can hardly find fault with the one who denies that all happens by necessity; for on his own theory this very argument is voiced by necessity” [V.S. 40], not by independent truthfulness... We are entitled to believe our brain is able to develop its 'applications' negating some external necessities by flight or shelters.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Giampaolo zennaro</name></author>	</entry>

