&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurus' Philosophy is more deductive (with critical awareness) than generally has been thought, &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;modelling &lt;/del&gt;itself, after Euclid, by &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;intuitive postulates &lt;/del&gt;''ai dôdeca stocheiôsis'' [U56]&amp;#160; the '''Twelve Elementary Propositions'''. 1 Matter is uncreatable, 2 Matter is &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;indistructible&lt;/del&gt;, 3 The universe consists of solid bodies and void , 4 Solid bodies are either compounds or simple, 5 The multitude of atoms is infinite, 6 The void is infinite in extent, 7 The atoms are always in motion, 8 The speed of atomic motion is uniform, 9 Motion is linear in space, vibratory in compounds&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, &lt;/del&gt;10 Atoms are capable of swerving slightly at any point in space or time, 11 Atoms are characterized by three qualities, weight, shape and size,&amp;#160; 12 The number of the different shapes is not infinite, merely innumerable.&amp;#160; All former propositions are primary knowledge, secondary &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;is &lt;/del&gt;derivative (from DRN books I-II, and De Witt)&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;; &lt;/del&gt;only ''antimartyrêsis''/falsifiability and non-counter-claim (''ouk antimartyrêsis'') are inductive. He realizes that postulates and derivative propositions ('words&amp;#160; explanation' [''On Nature XXV'']) cannot be debatable (we say analytic propositions are tautological), but “ If you arbitrarily reject [...] every intuitive faculty of mind, you will impute trouble to all other sensory experiences, thereby rejecting every criterion” [P.D. 24]. So, for our life completeness, living with pleasure (sensory experience), total demonstrability is not necessary, as Demetrius the Laconian says: &amp;quot; In the work entitled ''Kyriai Doxai'', Epicurus says that the [end is pleasure] [teaching that] it [needs] no demonstration&amp;quot; [''Textual Aporias'' fr. 52, Pherc 1012, Delattre]. His intuitive deductive ''physiologia'' has been almost strengthened by our physics&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;. It &lt;/del&gt;is a result &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;of &lt;/del&gt;scientific epistemology that has excluded any authoritarian dogmatism but fear of positive law (P.D. 34, “injustice is not an evil in and by itself”), and an elementary ''prolêpsis'' of justice, “not to inflict nor allow harm” and “to benefit human interactions” (usefulness), that does not include distributive justice, nor a standard of punishment that are relative ''ypolêpseis''&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, &lt;/del&gt;that is 'agreements'. He needed a philosophy of&amp;#160; ''ataraxia'', free from vain hopes, fear of Gods and guilty feelings and a world outlook set out by limits toward ''isonomia'', balance of opposites and ''katastematik'' stable desires.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;Epicurean 'signs/designations' (''semeioseon'') are an “observable basis of analogical inference and transition by similarity (''kath' omoiotêta metabasis'') to unobserved or unobservable” [De Lacy, ''On Infer'' p. 157].&amp;#160; “... so all natures that are grasped by application acts which move toward the unobservable&amp;#160; we will see them&amp;#160; if we look at the similarities which ...” [Epicurus, ''On Nature'' XXXIV (PHerc. 1451) Col. XI].&amp;#160; “These bodies (i.e. atoms) cannot be grasped but by reason [...] They have their own forms which cannot be grasped but by reason” [Plutarch, ''Opinions of Philosophers'', about Epicurus]. &lt;/ins&gt;Epicurus' Philosophy is more deductive (with critical awareness) than generally has been thought, &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;modeling &lt;/ins&gt;itself, after Euclid, by ''ai dôdeca stocheiôsis'' [U56]&amp;#160; the '''Twelve Elementary Propositions''' &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;after Euclid intuitive postulates&lt;/ins&gt;. 1 Matter is uncreatable, 2 Matter is &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;Indistructible&lt;/ins&gt;, 3 The universe consists of solid bodies and void , 4 Solid bodies are either compounds or simple, 5 The multitude of atoms is infinite, 6 The void is infinite in extent, 7 The atoms are always in motion, 8 The speed of atomic motion is uniform, 9 Motion is linear in space, vibratory in compounds &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;10 Atoms are capable of swerving slightly at any point in space or time, 11 Atoms are characterized by three qualities, weight, shape and size,&amp;#160; 12 The number of the different shapes is not infinite, merely innumerable.&amp;#160; All former propositions are primary knowledge, secondary &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;are &lt;/ins&gt;derivative (from DRN books I-II, and De Witt)&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, &lt;/ins&gt;only ''antimartyrêsis''/falsifiability and non-counter-claim (''ouk antimartyrêsis'') are inductive.&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;As Stoics reasoned necessity principle with a logical proposition - that says nothing about actual weather conditions - ('tomorrow it'll raining or not raining': it's necessary and ''tertium non datur''),&amp;#160; Epicurus likely and logically deduced that sometime necessity is not there, since 'all is necessary' is logically self confuting. Human trial-and-error synaptic links, alias soul's atoms course, are not programmed &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;from &lt;/del&gt;somebody and knowledge can't define its future beliefs and our ensuing innovatory deeds. &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;He realizes that postulates and derivative propositions ('words&amp;#160; explanation' [''On Nature XXV'']) cannot be debatable (we say analytic propositions are tautological), but “ If you arbitrarily reject [...] every intuitive faculty of mind, you will impute trouble to all other sensory experiences, thereby rejecting every criterion” [P.D. 24]. So, for our life completeness, living with pleasure (sensory experience), total demonstrability is not necessary, as Demetrius the Laconian says: &amp;quot; In the work entitled ''Kyriai Doxai'', Epicurus says that the [end is pleasure] [teaching that] it [needs] no demonstration&amp;quot; [''Textual Aporias'' fr. 52, Pherc 1012, Delattre]. &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;His intuitive deductive ''physiologia'' has been almost strengthened by our &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;empiric &lt;/ins&gt;physics&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;; nevertheless “theory can be tried out by experiment, but there &lt;/ins&gt;is &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;no way that leads from experiment to the birth of &lt;/ins&gt;a &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;theory” [A. Einstein, cit. by Vallentin A. ''Einstein'' (1965) p.105].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Total necessity would imply that '''all''' atoms have a '''linear, one-way, external causality''' Epicurus graphically designed&amp;#160; as linear&amp;#160; and parallel movement of atoms; non necessity, as a swerve, implying a crossroad/node with affirmation or negation; multiple explanation &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;implies &lt;/del&gt;a 'tree' causality, a conglomerate 'vibration' is a circuit causality or retro-action loop. Since the thought (immediate and complex atoms movement) has '''negation''' capability ''antimartyrêsis'', - i.e. no one-way straight motion, so there must be there some soul atoms alternative ways/crossroads (and a 'tree' choice) without necessity, that is with steering (''paregklisis''/swerve) as may be watched in capillary vessels.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;Epicurus&amp;#160; achievements&amp;#160; &lt;/ins&gt;result &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;from his &lt;/ins&gt;scientific epistemology that has excluded any authoritarian dogmatism but &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;fear &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;of positive law (P.D. 34, “injustice is not an evil in and by itself”), and an elementary ''prolêpsis'' of justice, “not to inflict nor allow harm” and “to benefit human interactions” (usefulness), that does not include distributive justice, nor a standard of punishment that are relative ''ypolêpseis'' that is 'agreements'. He needed a philosophy of&amp;#160; ''ataraxia'', free from vain hopes, fear of Gods and guilty feelings and a world outlook set out by limits toward ''isonomia'', balance of opposites and ''katastematik'' stable desires &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;that we can control&lt;/ins&gt;.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;It was no far-fletched logicism about Physics: today Networks Theory – starting from Poincaré and Euler - considers non linear causality;&amp;#160; the very artificial thought/cybernetic designs&amp;#160; a web of retro-actions/feedbacks, which say no to deterministic second principle of thermodynamics (' '''negative'''- entropy', order trend, creativity).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;As Stoics reasoned necessity principle with a logical proposition - that says nothing about actual weather conditions - &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;('tomorrow it'll raining or not raining' : it's necessary and ''tertium non datur''),&amp;#160; Epicurus likely and logically deduced that sometime necessity is not there, since 'all is necessary' is logically self confuting. Human trial-and-error synaptic links, alias soul's atoms course, are not programmed &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;by &lt;/ins&gt;somebody and knowledge can't define its future beliefs and our ensuing innovatory deeds.&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;A necessity theorist cannot demonstrate his opposer is wrong, since he couldn't freely be in agreement with the opposite point of view that his personal necessity &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/del&gt;unfairly &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;don&lt;/del&gt;'t allow, and bestows no alternative (negation) to his way of thinking (nor the improvement of kinetic desires): “He who says that all things happen by necessity can hardly find fault with the one who denies that all happens by necessity; for on his own theory this very argument is voiced by necessity” [V.S. 40], not by independent truthfulness... We are entitled to believe our brain is able to develop its 'applications' negating some external necessities by flight or shelters.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Total necessity would imply that '''all''' atoms have a '''linear, one-way, external causality''' Epicurus graphically designed&amp;#160; as linear&amp;#160; and parallel movement of atoms; non necessity, as a swerve, implying a crossroad/node with affirmation or negation; multiple explanation &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;and choice imply &lt;/ins&gt;a 'tree' causality, a conglomerate 'vibration' is a circuit causality or retro-action loop&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, where affirmation or negation act against the subject itself, under omeostasis, so as to preserve the conglomerate&lt;/ins&gt;. Since the thought (immediate and complex atoms movement) &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;has '''negation''' capability ''antimartyrêsis'', - i.e. no one-way straight motion, so there must be there some soul atoms alternative ways/crossroads &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;(and a 'tree' choice) &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;without necessity, that is with steering (''paregklisis''/swerve) as may be watched in capillary vessels &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;(today synapses)&lt;/ins&gt;.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Everything happens by necessity being self-confuting and '''there is always negation''' being self-confuting too (since one is affirming it) imply that&amp;#160; ''' 'Not everything' ''' happens by necessity - as a contrary- may be true under situations&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, and that &lt;/del&gt;sometime is there necessity,&amp;#160; sometime necessity is not, since one can choose after his own desires [like says D.L. 134]. Non necessity, as a swerve, implies a crossroad/node (instead of vessels ... today synapses)&amp;#160; with affirmation or negation; that a negation is there into one's mind one is sure, since denying &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;it &lt;/del&gt;is the evidence of its existence, and that's enough for one's pleasure attainableness and freedom, the negation of some external causality. &amp;quot;Concentrated together [atoms], [...] are by nature capable of producing such things and starting such a process&amp;quot; [ ''On Nature'' Book XXV PHerc&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;. &lt;/del&gt;697, [34. 4] ARR.&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;].&amp;#160; (&lt;/del&gt;“mind's primitive constitution” ”with its own causality” &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;[ &lt;/del&gt;''Perì Physeos'' VIII Pap. 1056/697/1191.7. Arrighetti]. Since the age of two, the human being can always say no in every situation, hopefully with thoughtfulness.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;It was no far-fletched &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;logicism about Physics: today Networks Theory – starting from Poincaré and Euler - &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;considers non linear causality;&amp;#160; the very artificial thought/cybernetic designs&amp;#160; a web of retro-actions/feedbacks, which say no to deterministic second principle of thermodynamics (' '''negative'''- entropy', order trend, creativity).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;From the same reasoning, as one cannot determine &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;natural &lt;/del&gt;desires, Epicurus inferred that negation - as a constituent element of the world - implies also limitation of freedom &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;(&lt;/del&gt;''elachiston''&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;)&lt;/del&gt;, and ''isonomia'' (balancing of opposites) can be theorized: &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;A necessity theorist cannot demonstrate his opposer is wrong, since he couldn't freely be in agreement with the opposite point of view that &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;his personal necessity unfairly &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;doesn&lt;/ins&gt;'t allow, and bestows no alternative (negation) to his way of thinking (nor the improvement of kinetic desires): “He who says that all things happen by necessity can hardly find fault with the one who denies that all happens by necessity; for on his own theory this very argument is voiced by necessity” [V.S. 40], not by independent truthfulness... We are entitled to believe our brain is able to develop its 'applications' negating some external necessities by flight or shelters.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The fall (eternal movement) of all atoms (not only soul's atoms) must have a non straight linear motion (i.e. have ''paregklisis''/swerve), &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/del&gt;because there is evidence of provisional agglomerates, and these atoms compounds have no straight but reticular vibrating motion, hence with rebound/negation or aggregation/affirmation; no atom is outside, since it is limited by the whole, it has an uncountable variability, but not infinite.&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Everything happens by necessity being self-confuting and '''there is always negation''' being self-confuting too (since one is affirming it) imply that&amp;#160; ''' 'Not everything' ''' happens by necessity - as a contrary- may be true under situations&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;; &lt;/ins&gt;sometime is there necessity,&amp;#160; sometime necessity is not, since one can choose after his own desires [like says D.L. 134]. Non necessity, as a swerve, implies a crossroad/node &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;(instead of vessels ... today synapses)&amp;#160; with affirmation or negation; that a negation is there into one's mind one is sure, since denying is the evidence of its existence, &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;and that's enough for one's pleasure attainableness and freedom, the negation of some external causality. &amp;quot;Concentrated together [atoms], [...] are by nature capable of producing such things and starting such a process&amp;quot; [ ''On Nature'' Book XXV PHerc 697, [34. 4] ARR.&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;; see Talk:Canon; and &lt;/ins&gt;“mind's primitive constitution” ”with its own causality” &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; (&lt;/ins&gt;''Perì Physeos'' VIII Pap. 1056/697/1191.7. Arrighetti&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;)&lt;/ins&gt;]. Since the age of two, the human being can always say no in every situation, hopefully with thoughtfulness. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Our pleasure is limited by necessary (that is invariable nervous and chemical response) body instincts, so it cannot grow, no positive freedom. That implies aloofness (by some more inward looking persons) from ambitions (infinite &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;and mainly &lt;/del&gt;frustrating desires)&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;.&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;From the same reasoning, as one cannot determine &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;one's necessary &lt;/ins&gt;desires, Epicurus inferred that negation - as a constituent element of the world - implies also limitation of freedom&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, since swerve ''paregklisis'' - acting under minimum margin at a time &lt;/ins&gt;''elachiston''&lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;- &lt;/ins&gt;, and ''isonomia'' (balancing of opposites &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;and complementaries&lt;/ins&gt;) &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;clash against our atoms; so &lt;/ins&gt;can &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;it &lt;/ins&gt;be theorized:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The thought gets its own '''limited''' freedom from the swerve of atoms simulacra limited by other simulacra: &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;''&lt;/del&gt;prolêpseis&lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;'' &lt;/del&gt;cannot be demonstrated (axioms); logic is limited by common more or plus and ''epilogismos''; choice rises when there is a limit of an alternative (crossroad).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The fall (eternal movement) of all atoms (not only soul's atoms) must have a non straight linear motion (i.e. have ''paregklisis''/swerve), because there is evidence of provisional agglomerates, and these atoms compounds have no straight but reticular vibrating motion, hence with rebound/negation or aggregation/affirmation; no atom is outside, since it is limited by the whole, it has an uncountable variability, but not infinite.&amp;#160; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Gods cannot be outside of the whole too, hence they must have atomic internal causality,&amp;#160; they cannot be devoid of swerve,&amp;#160; they cannot deny external casualness, hence they cannot inspire prophets nor help mankind.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Our pleasure is limited by necessary (that is invariable nervous and chemical response) body instincts, so it cannot grow, no positive freedom. That implies aloofness (by some more inward looking persons) from ambitions (infinite frustrating desires)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*The thought gets its own '''limited''' freedom from the swerve of atoms &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;and &lt;/ins&gt;simulacra limited by other simulacra: &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;prolêpseis cannot be demonstrated (axioms); logic is limited by common more or plus and ''epilogismos''; choice rises when there is a limit of an alternative (crossroad).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;*Gods cannot be outside of the whole too, hence they must have atomic internal causality,&amp;#160; they cannot be devoid of swerve,&amp;#160; they cannot deny external &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;causality and &lt;/ins&gt;casualness, hence they cannot inspire prophets nor help mankind.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;''Prolêpsis/prôton ennoêma '', limit, ''epilogismos'', practical prudence have been great results of Epicurean epistemological pragmatic recycling of Skeptics and Sophists' negativism and moral extremism, against oversimplifications of preceding philosophers lined in religion and politics of their State.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;''Prolêpsis/prôton ennoêma '', limit &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;(''peras'')&lt;/ins&gt;, ''epilogismos'', practical prudence &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; (''phronêsis''), &lt;/ins&gt;have been great results of Epicurean epistemological pragmatic recycling of Skeptics and Sophists' negativism and moral extremism, against oversimplifications of preceding philosophers lined in religion and politics of their State. &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;We have seen that science&amp;#160; (''physiologia'') is object of search into the past experiences of&amp;#160; persons fond of knowledge, the ''philo-sophoi''. But the future and&amp;#160; hidden (''to adêlon'') purposes of people are not scientifically knowable, they are only questionable, and are the subject-matter of prudence: wise questions, frequently updated about evolving situation, readiness and flexibility of action, that is virtue (''arete''). The more wise questions are: desirability and attainability (''oroys tôn epithymiôn'', [P.D.XI]; ''tagathon men eyktêton'', [The Fourfold Remedy]; control of oneself,&amp;#160; of things and persons (a &amp;quot;disposition, of which we are master&amp;quot; [''diatesis ês êmeis kyrioi'' …] not the one &amp;quot;which is under the control of others&amp;quot; [Diog. Oin., Fr. 112 ]). &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;We have seen that science&amp;#160; (''physiologia'') is object of search into the past experiences of&amp;#160; persons fond of knowledge, the ''philo-sophoi''. But the future and&amp;#160; hidden (''to adêlon'') purposes of people are not scientifically knowable, they are only questionable, and are the subject-matter of prudence: wise questions, frequently updated about evolving situation, readiness and flexibility of action, that is virtue (''arete''). The more wise questions are: desirability and attainability (''oroys tôn epithymiôn'', [P.D.XI]; ''tagathon men eyktêton'', [The Fourfold Remedy]; control of oneself,&amp;#160; of things and persons (a &amp;quot;disposition, of which we are master&amp;quot; [''diatesis ês êmeis kyrioi'' …] not the one &amp;quot;which is under the control of others&amp;quot; [Diog. Oin., Fr. 112 ]). Non necessary desires, compared to necessities&amp;#160; are&amp;#160; secondary and each other substituable. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Non necessary desires, compared to necessities&amp;#160; are&amp;#160; secondary and each other substituable. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Easiness of life is almost achievable by living secluded from crowd, by justice and indulgence with servants, by not deeply getting involved into love of women, by choice of sage persons and by wary reciprocation of favors between friends&amp;#160; discussed in ''On Gifts and Gratitude'' (''Perì dôrôn kai charitos'').&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Easiness of life is almost achievable by living secluded from crowd, by justice and indulgence with servants, by not deeply getting involved into love of women, by choice of sage persons and by wary reciprocation of favors between friends&amp;#160; discussed in ''On Gifts and Gratitude'' (''Perì dôrôn kai charitos'').&amp;lt;br&amp;gt; &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Prudence is made by questions, so most of all the Epicurean has to ask himself: “What will happen to me if that which this desire seeks is attained, and what if it is not?” [V.S. 71], putting into practice ''symmetrêsis&amp;#160; &amp;lt;kai&amp;gt; sympherônton kay asymphorôn'' [''Menoec''. 130] the “empirical calculation&amp;#160; of advantages and of harms”, and the ''eklogisis'' and&amp;#160; ''epilogismòs'', in analogy with preceding decisions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Prudence is made by questions, so most of all the Epicurean has to ask himself: “What will happen to me if that which this desire seeks is attained, and what if it is not?” [V.S. 71], putting into practice ''symmetrêsis&amp;#160; &amp;lt;kai&amp;gt; sympherônton kay asymphorôn'' [''Menoec''. 130] the “empirical calculation&amp;#160; of advantages and of harms”, and the ''eklogisis'' and&amp;#160; ''epilogismòs'', in analogy with preceding decisions. “Reckon into yourself not only about the 'more' but also about the 'less' [...]. If you got it at length, you are replete; if not at length, you are not still addicted […]&amp;#160; Is this a bafflement? You'll be alive as much easily as you lived before. [...] What we seek and by long job we compete about, we have to look into whether nothing in it is awkward or more than awkward: that is empty, these are dearly” [Sen. ''Ep'' 42, 6]. I appreciate what it is keeping up, but if it blows away, I give back it and I cut me off by my virtue” [Hor., ''Carmina'' III, 29, 41].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;“Reckon into yourself not only about the 'more' but also about the 'less' [...]. If you got it at length, you are replete; if not at length, you are not still addicted […]&amp;#160; Is this a bafflement? You'll be alive as much easily as you lived before. [...] What we seek and by long job we compete about, we have to look into whether nothing in it is awkward or more than awkward: that is empty, these are dearly” [Sen. ''Ep'' 42, 6]. I appreciate what it is keeping up, but if it blows away, I give back it and I cut me off by my virtue” [Hor., ''Carmina'' III, 29, 41].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;In case of impossible solution “Take up these sentences. We bother either by present or future troubles. About the present ones it's easy: if your body is free and without painful health , you wait and see, for now no work. Nobody is unlucky only by present” [Sen. ''Ep''. 13,7].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;In case of impossible solution “Take up these sentences. We bother either by present or future troubles. About the present ones it's easy: if your body is free and without painful health , you wait and see, for now no work. Nobody is unlucky only by present” [Sen. ''Ep''. 13,7].&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</summary>
		<author><name>Giampaolo zennaro</name></author>	</entry>

