				&lt;tr style='vertical-align: top;'&gt;
				&lt;td colspan='2' style=&quot;background-color: white; color:black; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;← Older revision&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td colspan='2' style=&quot;background-color: white; color:black; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Revision as of 10:08, 27 January 2015&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 2:&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot; class=&quot;diff-lineno&quot;&gt;Line 2:&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurean 'signs/designations' (''semeioseon'') are an “observable basis of analogical inference and transition by similarity (''kath' omoiotêta metabasis'') to unobserved or unobservable” [De Lacy, ''On Infer'' p. 157].&amp;#160; “... so all natures that are grasped by application acts which move toward the unobservable&amp;#160; we will see them&amp;#160; if we look at the similarities which ...” [Epicurus, ''On Nature'' XXXIV (PHerc. 1451) Col. XI].&amp;#160; “These bodies (i.e. atoms) cannot be grasped but by reason [...] They have their own forms which cannot be grasped but by reason” [Plutarch, ''Opinions of Philosophers'', about Epicurus]. Indeterminism of the swerve is analogous to logic incompleteness theorem: see Talk: Vatican Saying 40.&amp;#160; &amp;quot;existence of&amp;#160; dimension in atom,&amp;#160; we have asserted it after analogy with visible things&amp;quot;&amp;#160; [''Herod. L''. 59; it depends on internal inseparable minima, distinguished by not perceptible limits (''perata'') ]. This causes different behaviors of each atom.&amp;#160; 'After analogy', Epicurus guesses electrons involvement of thinking:&amp;#160; “the soul is a fine-structured material [...] It resembles a wind in some respects and heat in others [… but]&amp;#160; its fine structure makes it greatly different from both [Herod 063; there are ] an unimaginable number of atomic shapes […] which would defy observation” [Herod 043]. &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Epicurean 'signs/designations' (''semeioseon'') are an “observable basis of analogical inference and transition by similarity (''kath' omoiotêta metabasis'') to unobserved or unobservable” [De Lacy, ''On Infer'' p. 157].&amp;#160; “... so all natures that are grasped by application acts which move toward the unobservable&amp;#160; we will see them&amp;#160; if we look at the similarities which ...” [Epicurus, ''On Nature'' XXXIV (PHerc. 1451) Col. XI].&amp;#160; “These bodies (i.e. atoms) cannot be grasped but by reason [...] They have their own forms which cannot be grasped but by reason” [Plutarch, ''Opinions of Philosophers'', about Epicurus]. Indeterminism of the swerve is analogous to logic incompleteness theorem: see Talk: Vatican Saying 40.&amp;#160; &amp;quot;existence of&amp;#160; dimension in atom,&amp;#160; we have asserted it after analogy with visible things&amp;quot;&amp;#160; [''Herod. L''. 59; it depends on internal inseparable minima, distinguished by not perceptible limits (''perata'') ]. This causes different behaviors of each atom.&amp;#160; 'After analogy', Epicurus guesses electrons involvement of thinking:&amp;#160; “the soul is a fine-structured material [...] It resembles a wind in some respects and heat in others [… but]&amp;#160; its fine structure makes it greatly different from both [Herod 063; there are ] an unimaginable number of atomic shapes […] which would defy observation” [Herod 043]. &amp;#160;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;In analogy with round-table moderator and linguistics communication channel, a systems and cybernetic theory principle&amp;#160; of&amp;#160; 'subordination of parts' is plainly enounced in ''DRN'' 3.282-5, and a materialistic theory of emergent mind: ''Est necesse ventus et aer et calor vigeant commixtus inter se per artus atque aliud magis aliis subsit et emineat ut quiddam unum videatur fieri ab omnibus'': “It's a physical necessity that wind, air and heat [basic component forces] interact each other throughout limbs, and moreover a stronger than others quiddity [for us it will be the electrochemical network...] be hidden and surpasses in order an unitary whole be felt happen by others”.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;In analogy with round-table moderator and linguistics communication channel, a systems and cybernetic theory principle&amp;#160; of&amp;#160; 'subordination of parts' is plainly enounced in ''DRN'' 3.282-5, and a materialistic theory of emergent mind: ''Est necesse ventus et aer et calor vigeant commixtus inter se per artus atque aliud magis aliis subsit et emineat ut quiddam unum videatur fieri ab omnibus'': “It's a physical necessity that wind, air and heat [basic component forces] interact each other throughout limbs, and moreover a stronger than others quiddity [for us it will be the electrochemical network...] be hidden and surpasses in order an unitary whole be felt happen by others”.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;−&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #ffe49c; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Psychophysical parallelism is shown some more. Straightforward movement (necessity&amp;#160; ''anagke'' prevails) of atoms is open to random slightly angled swerve/''paregklisis'' (''Nec regione loci certa nec tempore certo'' [''DRN'', 2.293; 2. 218-219; 259-260;],&amp;#160; ''nec plus quam minimum'',&amp;#160; translation of ''elachiston'' [''DRN'', II, 244]; [today quantum jump]: chance / ''tychê'' prevails; and randomness&amp;#160; is open to agglomeration, to catalytic system loops and stability: constructiveness prevails.&amp;#160; In few planets&amp;#160; rocks and&amp;#160; Metals' agglomeration&amp;#160; are roused by ring&amp;#160; and helical forms of tetragonal carbon compounds.&amp;#160; Causality and materialism are not contradicted; actually linear causality is updated by net-like causality,&amp;#160; so as&amp;#160; DNA replication is a sort of negation/feedback of ''anagke/tyche''; ''par êmas'' 'up to one's own decisions' appears out of timelessness, as carbo-compounds feel time. No oneness nor naïve bidimensional determinism.&amp;#160; A tridimensional interaction among&amp;#160;  anagke-par êmas-tychê' bear indeterminacy principle: '' kata to pleon ê elatton'', the more or less of existence which expresses itself pragmatically into prudence and techniques, experiences of the possible &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/del&gt;and freedom. &lt;del class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt; &lt;/del&gt;Turing too believed that quanta's indeterminacy was conditions for&amp;#160; neg-entropy and freedom. Epicurus did not affirm (numerically or logicallly) 'laws' but '''limits''' (a trend): necessary fall (motion) of atoms is limited by indeterministic&amp;#160; swerve to run and create '''limited ''' things.. Unlimited organic creation of beings (kinetic desire)&amp;#160; of palaeo-reptilians is limited by 'up-to-us' ''katastêma'' and the prudence of mammalia and antropoids. So straightforward necessary desires (blind desire prevails) are open to exploratory moving desires: moving variation/''poikilma'' prevails; exploratory desires are open to moderate stability of ''epilogismos'' in accordance with deliberate choice: manifest mind prevails ; 'subordination of parts' principle over automatisms prevails. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;color:black; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #a3d3ff; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Psychophysical parallelism is shown some more. Straightforward movement (necessity&amp;#160; ''anagke'' prevails) of atoms is open to random slightly angled swerve/''paregklisis'' (''Nec regione loci certa nec tempore certo'' [''DRN'', 2.293; 2. 218-219; 259-260;],&amp;#160; ''nec plus quam minimum'',&amp;#160; translation of ''elachiston'' [''DRN'', II, 244]; [today quantum jump]: chance / ''tychê'' prevails; and randomness&amp;#160; is open to agglomeration, to catalytic system loops and stability: constructiveness prevails.&amp;#160; In few planets&amp;#160; rocks and&amp;#160; Metals' agglomeration&amp;#160; are roused by ring&amp;#160; and helical forms of tetragonal carbon compounds.&amp;#160; Causality and materialism are not contradicted; actually linear causality is updated by net-like causality,&amp;#160; so as&amp;#160; DNA replication is a sort of negation/feedback of ''anagke/tyche''; ''par êmas'' 'up to one's own decisions' appears out of timelessness, as carbo-compounds feel time. No oneness nor naïve bidimensional determinism.&amp;#160; A tridimensional interaction among&amp;#160;  anagke-par êmas-tychê' bear indeterminacy principle: '' kata to pleon ê elatton'', the more or less of existence which expresses itself pragmatically into prudence and techniques, experiences of the possible &lt;ins class=&quot;diffchange diffchange-inline&quot;&gt;, multiple explanations (e.g. today wave–particle duality) &lt;/ins&gt;and freedom. Turing too believed that quanta's indeterminacy was conditions for&amp;#160; neg-entropy and freedom. Epicurus did not affirm (numerically or logicallly) 'laws' but '''limits''' (a trend): necessary fall (motion) of atoms is limited by indeterministic&amp;#160; swerve to run and create '''limited ''' things.. Unlimited organic creation of beings (kinetic desire)&amp;#160; of palaeo-reptilians is limited by 'up-to-us' ''katastêma'' and the prudence of mammalia and antropoids. So straightforward necessary desires (blind desire prevails) are open to exploratory moving desires: moving variation/''poikilma'' prevails; exploratory desires are open to moderate stability of ''epilogismos'' in accordance with deliberate choice: manifest mind prevails ; 'subordination of parts' principle over automatisms prevails. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Complementariness is a form of reference/inference too (“If we infer this from signs, clearly we do so either by analogy or by contraposition” [Phld. ''On infer.'', 12. De Lacy]). Formation of a world is a matter of aggregation, balancing (''isonomia'') atoms shocks with atoms hooks (for us: 'valence bonds'); formation of life balances external generating movement (shocks) with autonomous movement (smooth movements) [already clarified by Aristotle 's ''Methaphysics''&amp;#160; Book VIII, chapter 4 : “inanimate objects are always moved by something from outside, but we say that the living creature moves itself.”]. Parallely, life balances atom's chance swerve with targetable movements [fundamental for us: homeostasis/feedback, early replication RNA, chlorophyllous photosynthesis,&amp;#160; tropisms]. These movements are symbolized a by loop, pendulum, balance.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Complementariness is a form of reference/inference too (“If we infer this from signs, clearly we do so either by analogy or by contraposition” [Phld. ''On infer.'', 12. De Lacy]). Formation of a world is a matter of aggregation, balancing (''isonomia'') atoms shocks with atoms hooks (for us: 'valence bonds'); formation of life balances external generating movement (shocks) with autonomous movement (smooth movements) [already clarified by Aristotle 's ''Methaphysics''&amp;#160; Book VIII, chapter 4 : “inanimate objects are always moved by something from outside, but we say that the living creature moves itself.”]. Parallely, life balances atom's chance swerve with targetable movements [fundamental for us: homeostasis/feedback, early replication RNA, chlorophyllous photosynthesis,&amp;#160; tropisms]. These movements are symbolized a by loop, pendulum, balance.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Formation of sage's atomic mind balances instinctual body movements (drives) with deliberate choice (reflection): “Even if they have the same mark (of&amp;#160; primitive [for us: 'genetic'] constitution), however we don't deprive&amp;#160; mind movement of its own causality; even if we make between it and atomic constitution a same matter, we forgive the latter, the former we don't believe (it must be)” [Epicurus,&amp;#160; ''Pap. 1056'' 7.VI; Arr. fr.&amp;#160; 34. 25].&amp;#160; Katastematic pleasure is described as a movement with&amp;#160; its own causality (human nature) and&amp;#160; its own reachable stable target, a smooth movement.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class='diff-marker'&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;background-color: #f9f9f9; color: #333333; font-size: 88%; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 4px; border-radius: 0.33em; border-color: #e6e6e6; vertical-align: top; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Formation of sage's atomic mind balances instinctual body movements (drives) with deliberate choice (reflection): “Even if they have the same mark (of&amp;#160; primitive [for us: 'genetic'] constitution), however we don't deprive&amp;#160; mind movement of its own causality; even if we make between it and atomic constitution a same matter, we forgive the latter, the former we don't believe (it must be)” [Epicurus,&amp;#160; ''Pap. 1056'' 7.VI; Arr. fr.&amp;#160; 34. 25].&amp;#160; Katastematic pleasure is described as a movement with&amp;#160; its own causality (human nature) and&amp;#160; its own reachable stable target, a smooth movement.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</summary>
